UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 247
1 AN ACT relating to schools and declaring an emergency.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 160.145 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) As used in this section:
5 (a) "Commercial, nonprofit, or local government affiliation" means:
6 1. Having an ownership interest in, being employed by, or using a
7 commercial business or activity;
8 2. An association with a nonprofit religious organization, organization
9 recognized as a patriotic or national organization in 36 U.S.C. sec.
10 20101 et seq., or other nonprofit organization granted a tax exemption
11 by the Internal Revenue Service under Section 501(c) of the Internal
12 Revenue Code; or
13 3. An association with a city, county, consolidated local government,
14 urban-county government, charter county government, or unified
15 local government;
16 (b) "Family member" means:
17 1. A parent, brother, sister, son, daughter, aunt, uncle, cousin, or
18 grandparent related to the student by consanguinity, affinity, or
19 adoption;
20 2. An adult that resides in the same household as the student; or
21 3. An emergency contact for the student provided by a parent;
22 (c)[ (b) ]"Parent" means a parent, legal guardian, a person acting as a parent in
23 the absence of a parent or guardian, or other individual[person] or agency
24 responsible for the[a] student;
25 (d) "Private electronic communication" means electronic communication that
26 involves direct one-on-one or group conversations that are only accessible
27 to the participants;
Page 1 of 9
