1 (e) "Qualified school volunteer" means an adult who:
2 1. Is not:
3 a. A school district employee; or
4 b. Enrolled in the school district; and
5 2. Has served the school or school district at any point during the current
6 school year:
7 a. As a student teacher, a nonfaculty coach or assistant coach, a
8 nonfaculty sponsor of an extracurricular program or activity, or
9 a school-sponsored academic tutor; or
10 b. In a nonfaculty student services role designated as a qualified
11 school volunteer by the local board of education;
12 (f)[(c)] "School district employee[ or volunteer]":
13 1. Means a school administrator, classified or contract employee who is
14 not enrolled in the school district that provides direct services to
15 students,[or] certified employee[ of a school district, school volunteer],
16 or compensated nonfaculty coach or assistant coach; and
17 2. Includes any Kentucky Department of Education or educational
18 cooperative employee who is assigned to a school or area technology
19 center within the school district on a full-time basis and granted
20 official access as a user of the traceable communication system[,
21 student teacher, or sponsor of an extracurricular program or activity];
22 (g)[ (d)] "Traceable communication system" means one (1) or more electronic
23 school notification and communication programs or applications that:
24 1. Are designated by a local board of education in accordance with
25 subsection (2) of this section;
26 2. Trace all communications sent to or by a student; and
27 3. Provide parents an opportunity to access and review those
