1 communications; and
2 (h)[(e)] "Unauthorized electronic communication":
3 1. Means private[an] electronic communication with a student enrolled in
4 a school district by the[a] school district's[district] employee or
5 qualified school volunteer who is not the student's family member that
6 occurs outside of a designated traceable communication system and
7 without prior written parental consent;[ and]
8 2. Includes any private electronic communication with a student or
9 students enrolled in the school district through a personal email
10 account, text messaging, social media, or other private electronic
11 [notification and ]communication program[programs] outside of the
12 traceable communication system; and[.]
13 3. Does not include:
14 a. Virtual school instruction;
15 b. Electronic translation services;
16 c. Electronic communication with any telephone number provided
17 by a parent for the purpose of school communication with that
18 parent;
19 d. Electronic communication in which a parent of the student is
20 included as a recipient or participant;
21 e. Voice communication on an official telephone number affiliated
22 with the school or school district;
23 f. Social media posts and comments that are not private electronic
24 communication;
25 g. Electronic communication related to commercial products or
26 services with a telephone number, email address, or other
27 electronic account affiliated with a lawful commercial business;
