1 h. Secure messaging for healthcare providers; or
2 i. Electronic communication between a school resource officer or
3 director of pupil personnel and a student in which the principal,
4 vice principal, or a school-based mental health services provider,
5 as defined in KRS 158.4416, is included as a recipient or
6 participant.
7 (2) Each local board of education shall designate a traceable communication system[ to
8 be the exclusive means] for [a ]school district employees and qualified school
9 volunteers[employee or volunteer] to communicate electronically with students
10 enrolled in the school district. The principal of each public school shall provide
11 parents written or electronic notification within the first ten (10) days of the school
12 year of each electronic school notification and communication program designated
13 within the traceable communication system. The notification shall include
14 instructions for parents to access and review communications sent through each
15 electronic school notification and communication program.
16 (3) (a) [Except as provided in subsections (4) and (5) of this section, ]A school
17 district employee or qualified school volunteer shall not engage in
18 unauthorized electronic communication[communicate electronically with a
19 student:
20 1. Outside of the traceable communication system designated by the local
21 board of education; or
22 2. Through an unauthorized electronic communication program or
23 application].
24 (b) A school district employee that violates paragraph (a) of this subsection
25 may[shall] be subject to disciplinary action in accordance with:
26 1. For certified employees, KRS 161.120 and 161.790; or
27 2. For classified employees, KRS 161.011(7).
