1 (c) A qualified school volunteer that violates paragraph (a) of this subsection
2 may[shall] be prohibited by the school district from future school volunteer
3 opportunities.
4 (4) A parent may submit written consent to authorize a designated school district
5 employee or qualified school volunteer who is not a family member to participate
6 in private electronic communication[communicate electronically] with his or her
7 child outside of the traceable communication system. The written consent:
8 (a) Shall be filed in the administrative office of the student's school;
9 (b) Shall be submitted to the administrative office of the school prior to any
10 private electronic communication being sent from a school district employee
11 or qualified school volunteer to a student outside of the traceable
12 communication system;
13 (c)[(b)] Shall designate each[a single,] specific school district employee or
14 qualified school volunteer[ per each consent form] that may participate in
15 private electronic communication[communicate] with the student outside of
16 the traceable communication system and shall not be transferable to any other
17 school district employee or qualified school volunteer;
18 (d)[(c)] May be revoked by the[a] parent who filed the consent at any time.
19 Upon notice of a revocation, the administrative office shall promptly notify
20 the school district and each school district employee and qualified school
21 volunteer subject to the revocation;
22 (e)[(d)] May establish terms limiting electronic communication with a student,
23 including [a term requiring that a parent be included as a direct party to all
24 electronic communications sent to the student outside of the traceable
25 communication system or ]establishing an expiration for the term of the
26 consent. Any electronic communication with the[a] student enrolled in the
27 school district outside of the traceable communication system under this
