1 subsection shall comply with all terms of the written consent;[ and]
2 (f) Shall not be rejected or denied by the school or school district unless the
3 written consent fails to properly identify the applicable student, school
4 district employee, or qualified school volunteer. Upon receipt of the written
5 consent, the administrative office shall deliver a copy of the written consent
6 to the school district and the designated school district employee or qualified
7 school volunteer;
8 (g) Shall not be compelled as a requirement for a student to participate in an
9 academic, athletic, or extracurricular opportunity; and
10 (h)[(e)] Shall not authorize a school district employee or qualified school
11 volunteer to engage in inappropriate or sexual electronic communication with
12 a student or be used as a basis of a defense for a school district employee or
13 qualified school volunteer that engages in inappropriate or sexual electronic
14 communication with a student or students.
15 (5) Notwithstanding subsections (2) and (3) of this section, this section shall not restrict
16 any private electronic communications:
17 (a) Between a student and his or her family member who is a school district
18 employee or qualified school volunteer;
19 (b) Between a student and a school district employee or qualified school
20 volunteer who reasonably believes an emergency exists that creates an
21 imminent risk to any person or property, provided the school district
22 employee promptly discloses the private electronic communication to his or
23 her immediate supervisor after the fact in accordance with subsection (7) of
24 this section;
25 (c) During and in direct relation to a school-sanctioned field trip the student
26 has parental consent to attend;
27 (d) During and in direct relation to work-based learning experiences; or
