1 (e) That are directly related to a commercial, nonprofit, or local government
2 affiliation that has been previously disclosed in accordance with subsection
3 (6) of this section.
4 (6) A school district employee or qualified school volunteer may submit a written
5 disclosure notifying the school district of a commercial, nonprofit, or local
6 government affiliation that could reasonably result in private electronic
7 communication with a student outside of the traceable communication system.
8 Upon filing the written disclosure, subsequent private electronic communication
9 directly related to the disclosed commercial, nonprofit, or local government
10 affiliation is no longer subject to the restrictions of subsections (2) and (3) of this
11 section in accordance with paragraph (5)(e) of section.
12 (7) (a) A school district employee or qualified school volunteer that participated in
13 unauthorized electronic communication subject to subsection (2) and (3) of
14 this section or reasonably believes[receives a report alleging] that another
15 school district employee or qualified school volunteer participated in
16 unauthorized electronic communication that is subject to subsections (2) and
17 (3) of this section that has not been previously reported shall immediately
18 notify the supervising principal or applicable supervisor. If the subject of the
19 report is the principal or a district-wide employee, the reporting employee or
20 volunteer shall immediately notify the superintendent of the school district. If
21 the subject of the report is the superintendent or a Kentucky Department of
22 Education employee assigned to a school or area technology center within
23 the school district on a full-time and continuing basis, the reporting
24 employee or volunteer shall immediately notify the commissioner of
25 education and the chair of the local board of education.
26 (b) A school district employee that violates paragraph (a) of this subsection
27 may[shall] be subject to disciplinary action in accordance with:
