1 1. For certified employees, KRS 161.120 and 161.790; or
2 2. For classified employees, KRS 161.011(7).
3 (8)[(7)] (a) Upon receipt of a report alleging that a school district employee or
4 qualified school volunteer violated subsection (2) or (3) of this
5 section[participated in unauthorized electronic communication], the
6 commissioner of education, a principal, or a superintendent shall immediately:
7 1. Notify the parent of each student that is an alleged party to the
8 unauthorized electronic communications; and
9 2. a. If the individual that is the subject of the report is a certified
10 employee:
11 i. Notify the Education Professional Standards Board, which
12 shall promptly investigate all allegations received under this
13 subsection and proceed with appropriate disciplinary actions
14 in accordance with KRS 161.120; and
15 ii. Investigate the underlying allegations and proceed with
16 appropriate disciplinary actions in accordance with KRS
17 161.790;
18 b. If the individual that is the subject of the report is a classified
19 employee, investigate the underlying allegations and proceed with
20 appropriate disciplinary actions in accordance with KRS
21 161.011(7);[ and]
22 c. If the individual that is the subject of the report is a qualified
23 school[ or district] volunteer, the school or district shall investigate
24 the underlying allegations and, if substantiated, the qualified
25 school volunteer may[shall] be prohibited from future school and
26 district volunteer opportunities; and
27 d. Notwithstanding any statute to the contrary, notify the parent of
