1 each student that is an alleged party to the unauthorized
2 electronic communication of each material phase of the
3 investigation and disciplinary action under this subparagraph,
4 including but not limited to a written summary of the results of
5 an investigation and the final outcome of the disciplinary action.
6 (b) A principal or superintendent who violates paragraph (a) of this subsection
7 shall be subject to disciplinary action in accordance with KRS 156.132 and
8 161.120.
9 Section 2. If a school district volunteer was prohibited from future school
10 volunteer opportunities pursuant to subsection (3)(c) of KRS 160.145 prior to the
11 effective date of this Act, a school district may permit that person to participate in future
12 school volunteer opportunities.
13 Section 3. Whereas it is critical to ensure that parents, schools, and school
14 districts have clarity on lawful electronic communication with students, an emergency is
15 declared to exist, this Act takes effect upon its passage and approval by the Governor or
16 upon its otherwise becoming a law.
